Reasoning: The paper discusses the concept of "Smart Cities" which involves the use of science- and data-driven urban design, retrofit, and operation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Science sub-categories that deal with intelligent systems, data analysis, and urban infrastructure. Specifically, cs.CY (Computers and Society), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) are likely candidates as they deal with the intersection of computer science and societal issues. Additionally, cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DB (Databases) are also possible sub-categories as they may be relevant to the security and management of data in smart cities.
